[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m trying to wrap my head around the challenge of defining the same binary class twice. It seems that I could use a custom child-first loader to define JmDNSV1 bytes from a resource, but I'd need the class bytes for v1 with the same name. There’s the option of incorporating JavaCompiler for dynamic class loading, but that might get too complicated and unsupported by native. 
